"title": "4654: horn",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4654",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The hard, pointed growth on the heads of certain animals; a projection resembling such a growth. The horns of animals were regarded as symbols of strength. In apocalyptic writings, horns may denote various powers and enemies of God. Altars were made with horn-like corner projections.</p>\n<h2>Horns of animals</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:13\">GEN 22:13</a>LEV <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:16\">11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:15\">DEU 14:15</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:21\">PSA 22:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:31\">PSA 69:31</a></p>\n<h2>Uses of animal horns</h2>\n<h3>As musical instruments</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:13\">EXO 19:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:4\">JOS 6:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:28\">1CH 15:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr15:14\">2CH 15:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:3\">PSA 81:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:6\">PSA 98:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:5\">DAN 3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:7\">DAN 3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:10\">DAN 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:15\">DAN 3:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:8\">HOS 5:8</a></p>\n<h3>As oil containers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:1\">1SA 16:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:39\">1KI 1:39</a></p>\n<h2>Uses of imitation horns</h2>\n<h3>As projections at corners of altars</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:2\">EXO 27:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:12\">EXO 29:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:2-Exod30:3\">EXO 30:2–30:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:10\">EXO 30:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:25-Exod37:26\">EXO 37:25–37:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:2\">EXO 38:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:7\">LEV 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:18\">LEV 4:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:25\">LEV 4:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:30\">LEV 4:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:34\">LEV 4:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:15\">LEV 8:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:9\">LEV 9:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:18\">LEV 16:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:50-1Kgs1:51\">1KI 1:50–1:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:28\">1KI 2:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:27\">PSA 118:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:1\">JER 17:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:15\">EZK 43:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:20\">EZK 43:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:14\">AMO 3:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:13\">REV 9:13</a></p>\n<h3>As prophetic signs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:11\">1KI 22:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:10\">2CH 18:10</a></p>\n<h2>Horns as symbols of strength</h2>\n<h3>Describing God's saving power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:2-2Sam22:3\">2SA 22:2–22:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:2\">PSA 18:2</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:69\">LUK 1:69</a></p>\n<h3>Describing human strength</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:17\">DEU 33:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:1\">1SA 2:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:10\">1SA 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps75:10\">PSA 75:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:17\">PSA 89:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:24\">PSA 89:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps92:10\">PSA 92:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps112:9\">PSA 112:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:17\">PSA 132:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps148:14\">PSA 148:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:25\">JER 48:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:3\">LAM 2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:17\">LAM 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek29:21\">EZK 29:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:21\">EZK 34:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:13\">MIC 4:13</a></p>\n<h3>Symbolising the power of world rulers and enemies of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:7-Dan7:25\">DAN 7:7–7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:3-Dan8:4\">DAN 8:3–8:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:5-Dan8:11\">DAN 8:5–8:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:19-Dan8:22\">DAN 8:19–8:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech1:18-Zech1:21\">ZEC 1:18–1:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:3-Rev12:9\">REV 12:3–12:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:1-Rev13:6\">REV 13:1–13:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:11-Rev13:14\">REV 13:11–13:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:3-Rev17:8\">REV 17:3–17:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:12-Rev17:17\">REV 17:12–17:17</a></p>\n<h3>Symbolising the power of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:6\">REV 5:6</a></strong></p>",
